import PyPDF2

pdf_path = '/workspace/benchmark/datasets/paper.pdf'
with open(pdf_path, 'rb') as f:
    reader = PyPDF2.PdfReader(f)
    num_pages = len(reader.pages)
    text = ''
    for i in range(num_pages):
        text += reader.pages[i].extract_text() + '\n'

# Find section 3.1 and extract its content (and a bit after for context)
import re
match = re.search(r'Section 3.1(.*?)(Section 3.2|Section 4|References|$)', text, re.DOTALL|re.IGNORECASE)
if match:
    section_3_1 = match.group(1)
else:
    # fallback: try to find "3.1" and grab some lines after
    m2 = re.search(r'3\.1[\s\S]{0,1000}', text)
    section_3_1 = m2.group(0) if m2 else 'NOT FOUND'

section_3_1[:2000]  # show first 2000 chars for inspection
